    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Arrangements now complete for tender in Washington, 15th instant, of
                            negotiable drafts payable London, English gold equivalent of Spanish
                            gold. If not already done, answer note of minister for foreign affairs
                            in response to yours of 18th June last, as directed in my telegram of
                            August 24.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
